data.chText: 为（某人）提供住宿（或膳宿、座位等）
data.enText: to provide sb with a room or place to sleep, live or sit

data.chText: 这家旅馆可供500位旅客住宿。
data.enText: The hotel can accommodate up to 500 guests.
to provide enough space for sb/sth

data.chText: 一张激光唱片可以容纳70多分钟的音乐。
data.enText: Over 70 minutes of music can be accommodated on one CD.
to consider sth, such as sb's opinion or a fact, and be influenced by it when you are deciding what to do or explaining sth

data.chText: 我们的提案尽量照顾到少数群体的特殊需要。
data.enText: Our proposal tries to accommodate the special needs of minority groups.
to help sb by doing what they want

data.chText: 我多次接受采访，已给了报界许多方便。
data.enText: I have accommodated the press a great deal, giving numerous interviews.
to change your behaviour so that you can deal with a new situation better

data.chText: 我需要适应新的时间表。
data.enText: I needed to accommodate to the new schedule.

simple_means.memory_skill: ac 加强 + com 共同 + mod 方式 + ate 表动词 → 方式相同 → 与…符合

means: 为(某人)提供住宿(或膳宿、座位等)

ex.chText: 过一会儿你的眼睛就能适应黑暗。
ex.enText: Your eyes will accommodate to the darkness after a while.

ex.chText: 她不得不使自己适应新的工作。
ex.enText: She had to accommodate to a new job.
He adapted to the new school.

ex.chText: 鲍勃改装了旧汽车，这样他的儿子便能使用。
ex.enText: Bob adapted his old car so his son could use it.

synonyms.bx: 强调改变现有条件以适应新的情况。

ex.chText: 他的眼睛还没有适应黑暗。
ex.enText: His eyes have't adjusted to the darkness yet.
Kids are quite good at adjusting.

synonyms.bx: 指稍微调整以适应特定工作或新的情况，调整幅度没有 adapt 大，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 这家饭店能接纳300个观光客。
代表们被安排在宾馆住宿。
ex.enText: The delegates were accommodated at the guest house.

ex.chText: 一些学生被安置在附近的住家中。
ex.enText: Some students were accommodated in homes nearby.

synonyms.bx: 用于正式场合，表示提供房间供客人暂住。

ex.chText: 在纽约逗留期间，我寄住在怀特太太家里。
ex.enText: I lodged with Mrs. White while I stayed in New York.

ex.chText: 这家旅店可以接待100个学生。
他以前租住的那栋楼后来变成一座教堂。
ex.enText: The building he was lodged in later became a church.

synonyms.bx: 指临时居住或为某人提供短时客居之所，一般要付房租。

ex.chText: 很抱歉，我不能留你住下，因此你得住旅店了。
ex.enText: I'm sorry I can't put you up, you'll have to stay in a hotel.

ex.chText: 他去探望约翰时投宿在一家假日酒店里。
ex.enText: He was put up at a holiday inn when he went to see John.

tr: make fit for, or change to suit a new purpose
example: Adapt our native cuisine to the available food resources of the new country
The scientists had to accommodate the new results with the existing theories

tr: provide a service or favor for someone
provide with something desired or needed
example: Can you accommodate me with a rental car?
We are lodging three foreign students this semester
The auditorium can't hold more than 500 people

value.def: If a building or space can accommodate someone or something, it has enough room for them.

example.ex: The school in Poldown was not big enough to accommodate all the children...
example.tran: 波尔登的学校不够大，容不下所有的孩子。

example.ex: The CD-ROMs will accommodate the works of all English poets from 600 to 1900.
example.tran: 这些光盘能存下从公元600年到1900年所有英国诗人的作品。

value.def: To accommodate someone means to provide them with a place to live or stay.

example.ex: ...a hotel built to accommodate guests for the wedding of King Alfonso...
example.tran: 一家为接待前来参加阿方索国王婚礼的来宾而建的宾馆

example.ex: Students are accommodated in homes nearby.
example.tran: 学生被安置在附近的住家中。

value.def: If something is planned or changed to accommodate a particular situation, it is planned or changed so that it takes this situation into account.

example.ex: The roads are built to accommodate gradual temperature changes...
example.tran: 修建这些道路时考虑到了温度的逐渐变化。

example.ex: The way that American history is taught may change in order to accommodate some more of those cultures.
example.tran: 美国历史的授课方式可能会为了照顾到更多的文化而作改变。

value.def: If you do something to accommodate someone, you do it with the main purpose of pleasing or satisfying them.

example.ex: He has never put an arm around his wife to accommodate photographers...
example.tran: 他从未为了迎合摄影师而搂住妻子。

example.ex: He's already altered several of the proposals in his economic plan to accommodate demands of special interests.
example.tran: 他已经改动了经济计划中的几项提议以迁就特殊利益集团的要求。

value.def: If you accommodate to something new, you change your behaviour or ideas so that you are able to deal with it.

example.ex: Some animal and plant species cannot accommodate to the rapidly changing conditions...
example.tran: 某些种类的动植物不能适应迅速变化的环境。

example.ex: She walked slowly to accommodate herself to his pace.
example.tran: 她走得很慢，以便与他保持一致的步伐。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = mode, manner 方式, 模式；风度
rootsaffixes.title: mod

partsOfSpeech.dec: ac 加强 + com 共同 + mod 方式，模式；风度 + ate 做，造成，使… → 方式相同 → 与…符合
com 共同 + mod 方式，模式；风度 + ious …的 → 大家都有〔地方〕的 → 宽敞的
com 共同 + mod 方式，模式；风度 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 有共同模式的东西 → 商品
mode 方式；样式 + l → 模型
moder〔= mod〕方式，模式；风度 + ate 具有…的，有…性质的 → 有度的 → 适度的
mod 方式，模式；风度 + est → 做事有风度 → 礼貌的
mod 方式，模式；风度 + ify 使 → 规范化 → 修改
mod 方式，模式；风度 + ul + ate 做，造成，使… → 对模式进行调整 → 调整
out 出 + mod 方式，模式；风度 + ed 表形容词 → 方式过了时 → 过时的
re 重新 + mod 方式，模式；风度 + el → 再造模型 → 改造
